[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating login module features**\n\nI'm considering the features not currently covered, like ResourcePrincipalsLoginModule and InstancePrincipalsLoginModule. It seems challenging to test without the right environment or metadata service. I wonder if testing the InstancePrincipals builder with a local server could help? There’s a need to inspect OCI auth sources and how login lifecycle methods function. \n\nI need to ensure I could handle tests on encrypted private keys while focusing on public API behavior. The technical details are quite overwhelming!\n\n**Exploring key generation options**\n\nI wonder if I can generate an encrypted key at test runtime using OpenSSL, but that might not be a good dependency. Using Java might work, but the tests are for a native image with no direct external access. I need to create a static encrypted private key and passphrase, ensuring it’s supported. \n\nIt’s tricky, but it could work using OpenSSL during analysis. I want to avoid deprecated APIs and ensure various logic flows are tested without duplication.\n\n**Testing provider registration**\n\nI'm thinking about how to test if the provider is automatically registered when any OciLoginModule class initializes through a static block, which means it shouldn't require an explicit initialization. It seems the existing loginModule static might be registered but not confirmed, which isn't very strong. \n\nI wonder if testing JAAS LoginContext integration with public login modules would be effective? Direct calls to initialize exist, but there's a new feature where OciLoginModule can be used through standard JAAS LoginContext config.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_006d6cdd5754fe15016a24a901880c81939413bb3e900a1840\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJKkUnX1pZ2dzLUoHbbNxZxX9KHYGL5GAW1y0bt3WYx3AW4wr97vWa1G5bXroNuov5o0HD2Y2c-zRhpV5bwi